From e22e106e5750bc80f41b8ef482a3f22ee23fc370 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Sertonix <sertonix@posteo.net>
Date: Fri, 27 Feb 2026 02:44:59 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] glycin/sandbox: detect bwrap blocked when "Failed to make /
 slave"

This error message shows up on the alpine linux x86 CI. It seems to
be possible in some container environments.

2026-02-27T01:35:46.976539Z DEBUG glycin::sandbox: Testing bwrap availability with: "bwrap" "--unshare-all" "--die-with-parent" "--chdir" "/" "--ro-bind" "/usr" "/usr" "--dev" "/dev" "--ro-bind-try" "/etc/ld.so.cache" "/etc/ld.so.cache" "--ro-bind-try" "/nix/store" "/nix/store" "--tmpfs" "/tmp-home" "--tmpfs" "/tmp-run" "--clearenv" "--setenv" "HOME" "/tmp-home" "--setenv" "XDG_RUNTIME_DIR" "/tmp-run" "--setenv" "RUST_LOG" "trace" "--setenv" "XDG_RUNTIME_DIR" "/builds/sertonix/aports/community/greetd-phrog/src/phrog-0.50.0" "--ro-bind" "/lib" "/lib" "--seccomp" "29" "/usr/bin/true"
2026-02-27T01:35:46.978624Z DEBUG glycin::sandbox: bwrap availability test returned: Output { status: ExitStatus(unix_wait_status(256)), stdout: "", stderr: "\u{1b}[2m2026-02-27T01:35:46.977222Z\u{1b}[0m \u{1b}[35mTRACE\u{1b}[0m \u{1b}[2mglycin::sandbox\u{1b}[0m\u{1b}[2m:\u{1b}[0m Using /proc/meminfo: MemAvailable:   31055180 kB\n\u{1b}[2m2026-02-27T01:35:46.977251Z\u{1b}[0m \u{1b}[35mTRACE\u{1b}[0m \u{1b}[2mglycin::sandbox\u{1b}[0m\u{1b}[2m:\u{1b}[0m Using /proc/meminfo: SwapFree:        7947336 kB\nSetting process memory limit\nbwrap: Failed to make / slave: Permission denied\n" } (Signal: None, Code: Some(1))
2026-02-27T01:35:46.978645Z DEBUG glycin::sandbox: bwrap sandboxing available: true

Ref https://github.com/containers/bubblewrap/issues/689
Ref https://github.com/containers/bubblewrap/issues/505
---
 glycin/src/sandbox.rs | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/glycin/src/sandbox.rs b/glycin/src/sandbox.rs
index 2e6d5a15..21b4becc 100644
--- a/glycin/src/sandbox.rs
+++ b/glycin/src/sandbox.rs
@@ -746,6 +746,7 @@ impl Sandbox {
                 // Wording of an old Debian patch
                 "No permissions to create new namespace",
                 "bwrap: setting up uid map: Permission denied",
+                "bwrap: Failed to make / slave: Permission denied",
             ]
             .iter()
             .any(|y| x.contains(y))
